## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of current data, as the technology and its implications are rapidly evolving. Additionally, the ethical and societal impacts of self-driving cars are complex and may not be fully understood until the technology is more widely adopted. Further research is needed to explore long-term effects and regulatory challenges.